{
  "primary_issue": "SQL injection vulnerability in deleteBanji operation",
  "evidence": "String id = request.getParameter(\"id\"); banjiDao.deleteBanji(id); The id parameter is taken directly from user input and passed to a DAO method without any validation or sanitization, likely leading to SQL injection.",
  "fix_summary": "Validate that the id parameter is a numeric value (e.g., using id.matches(\"\\\\d+\")) before passing it to deleteBanji, or use parameterized queries in the DAO layer."
}
